{"title": "Morality Adjustment", "content": "We have the Face\u0096Heel Turn, when a hero changes sides and becomes a villain. We have the Heel\u0096Face Turn, when instead a villain abandons ship (no, not that kind of ship) to become a hero. We even have the Heel\u0096Face Revolving Door, where they keep changing sides at the drop of a hat. But what about the part in between, when a character becomes more of either a Heel or a Face, but not far enough to leave the team?\n\nThat's what we call a Morality Adjustment. It comes in all different variations based on direction and extent, but we'll break it into four main flavours.\n\u2022 A villain becoming more of a Heel. (eg: from Villain to Complete Monster)\n\u2022 A villain becoming more of a Face. (eg: from Villain to Anti-Villain)\n\u2022 A hero becoming more of a Heel. (eg: from Hero to Anti-Hero)\n\u2022 A hero becoming more of a Face. (eg: from Hero to Ideal Hero)", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityAdjustment", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Slayers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheDCU", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DoctorWhoNewAdventures", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/LegendOfTheSeeker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CityOfHeroes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarWarsTheOldRepublic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperRobotWarsUX", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/AntiheroForHire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Magellan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/MandatoryRollerCoaster", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/MenageA3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/SandraOnTheRocks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TheOrderOfTheStick", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/OurLittleAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Gargoyles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/StarWarsTheCloneWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DarkDisciple"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/F